item.title: Feelin' alright
item.description: Seems I got to have a change of scene 'Cause every night I have the strangest dreams Imprisoned by the way it could have been Left here on my own or so it seems I got to leave before I start to scream But someone's locked the door and took the key You feelin' alright? I'm not feelin' too good myself Well, you feelin' alright? I'm not feelin' too good myself Boy you sure took me for one big ride Even now I sit and wonder why And when I think of you I start myself to cry out I just can't waste my time, I must keep dry Gotta stop believin' in all your lies 'Cause there's too much to do before I die, hey You feelin' alright?
